SYNOPSIS
========
   string get_ed_buffer_save_file_name(stringÂ edited_file)

DESCRIPTION
===========
   This function is called when an interactive user object is destructed or 
   loses connection through remove_interactive(E) while editing with ed(E) the
   file edited_file (emergency save). `this_player()` is set to the object 
   that lost connection. The function should return a file name for the 
   emergency save file.

   USAGE
   =====
      This breaks up file into its components and stores it in the user's 
      emergency save directory under the file's basename:

         string get_ed_buffer_save_file_name(string file) {
           return "/players/"+getuid(this_player())+"/.dead_ed_files/"
                  + explode(file, "/")[<1];
         }

SEE ALSO
========
   ed(E), destruct(E), remove_interactive(E), valid_write(M)
